cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use or implement this protocol, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Imprimatur — Model-Evaluated Competency Certificate Protocol"
authors:
  - name: "Nikša Barlović"
  - name: "Claude Sonnet 4.6"
    affiliation: "Anthropic"
repository-code: "https://github.com/catcam/imprimatur"
license: Apache-2.0
version: "1.1"
date-released: "2026-05-02"
doi: "10.5281/zenodo.19981460"
abstract: >
  Imprimatur is an open protocol for model-evaluated competency certification.
  An AI model evaluates a user through natural interaction and proposes certificates;
  an independent review model issues or rejects them. Certificates are published
  to Zenodo with a DOI, emailed as PDF, and verifiable by hash.
keywords:
  - AI evaluation
  - competency certificate
  - human-AI interaction
  - verifiable credentials
  - open protocol
